This article is a transcript of a teleconference call with senior administration officials previewing day one of President Biden's trip to Germany. The call is on background, meaning the information can be used but not attributed to a specific official. The officials discuss the President's meeting with German Chancellor Scholz and the agenda, which includes discussions on Russia, Ukraine, transatlantic defense issues, and global challenges like climate change and energy. They also mention the G7 Summit and its focus on the global economy and infrastructure. The officials announce that the G7 leaders will ban imports of Russian gold and discuss the ongoing efforts to pressure Russia. The call concludes with a Q&A session.